4.38/5  rDev -2%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Poured from a 375ml bottle into a tulip glass. Batch #6
A- Pours a deep chardonnay golden yellow color. Has a very high wine like clarity. Small fizzy head that dissipated quickly. 
S- Lots of sour apple, some vinegar, some light vanilla, good amount of oak. some white wine character in there. 
T- Similar to aroma but amplified to an insane degree. Lots of tart lemon, sour apple, and vinegar. Finishes with a dry yeasty note. Has that old barn cellar thing that sours usually have. 
M- Medium-light the flavor makes this a sipper. 
O- This is one of the most sour beers I've had and if you're looking for something that delivers in the pucker department seek this one out. It is also somewhat too sour for me in my tastes. It's missing a bit of the subtlety that I got from Supplication. Still an amazing beer and if you want to test the limits of sour seek it out. 873 charactersPaulyB83, Apr 16, 2014
