4.42/5  rDev -1.1%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4Huge thanks to akorsak for the bottle!
Batch 002
Pours a beautiful, clear, golden-yellow with a touch of orange. A small white head forms at first, but slowly subsides to a thin collar around the edges of the glass. A few patches of lacing here and there.
Vanilla oak infused with sour funk rises up from the glass. Swirling the glass brings out some sweet citrus acidity and hay. Earthy, slightly musty and a little grassy. Great nose.
Oak and a bit of funk hit the tongue, but these notes are immediately doused in a large wave of acidic sourness. Definitely the most sour beer I've had from Russian River. Green apple brett mixed with juicy oranges and peaches. Straw and hay with a nice fruitiness. Lemon juice acidity on the finish.
Mouthfeel is awesome. Smooth and slippery with perfect carbonation. Heavy sourness throughout. Crisp at times and always mouth watering.
Drinkability is good. This beer has turned into a beast with some age on it. Nice complexity in the nose and flavor, plus lots sourness. A sourhead's dream for sure. That being said, the level of sourness does cut down on the drinkability somewhat, but at the same time makes the beer fun to drink. I'll definitely have to seek out batch 003 now that I've had this. Highly recommended. 1,265 characterssisuspeed, Mar 15, 2011
4.8/5  rDev +7.4%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Poured into a wine glass, revealing crystal clear apricot body, some lush bubbles over a thin film. Amazing color, amazingly clear. I would like jewelry made out of this beer. Smells nice and funky with sweet clover honey and stone fruit. Some vanilla, some citrus.
