4.35/5  rDev -2.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4750ml bottle (batch 003) poured into my Russian River "Barrel Aged Ales" goblet (pretty ugly design though). Beatification is a spritzy gold with a large white head that leaves scattered lace. A nice crackle to the head, even though it is pretty quick to dissipate, impressive for what essentially is a gueze. 
